      <h2 id="retention-automation">Automating Your Retention Process</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none">
        <p>Automation ensures consistent customer touchpoints without overwhelming your team. Set up automated workflows that trigger based on customer behavior, service dates, and communication history. Companies using retention automation see 30% higher customer lifetime values compared to manual processes.</p>

        <p>Service follow-up automation should trigger within 24 hours of job completion. Include a satisfaction survey, maintenance agreement offer (if not enrolled), and contact information for future needs. This single touchpoint increases repeat business rates by 35% when implemented consistently.</p>

        <p>Maintenance reminder automation prevents customers from forgetting scheduled services. Send first reminders 30 days before due dates, second reminders 14 days before, and final reminders 3 days before. Include easy rescheduling links to reduce no-shows and maintain service momentum.</p>

        <p>Seasonal campaign automation reaches all customers at optimal times. Create campaigns for heating system prep (September), cooling system check-ups (March), indoor air quality assessments (January), and energy efficiency evaluations (May). Automated timing ensures consistent messaging regardless of staff workload.</p>

        <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
          <h4 style="margin-top: 0; color: #2e7d32;">Automation Workflow Example</h4>
